```class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> constructRectangle(int area) {
        int w = sqrt(area);
        while (area % w != 0) {
            w--;
        }
        return {area / w, w};
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(sqrt(area))
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: This solution uses the property of a rectangle that its area is the product of its length and width. It starts with the square root of the area as the width and decrements it until it finds a divisor of the area, which is the optimal width. The length is then calculated as the area divided by the width.

